You can use this program for free and give copies to friends but 
WE DON'T GIVE ANY WARRANTY FOR ANY DAMAGE THAT MAY BE CAUSED BY THIS PROGRAM.
Please read COPYING for details.

And please read the documentations on the homepage:
http://www.anitmt.org/      

Read INSTALL for details on compilation.

In order to make an animation you have to create a pov scene, an adl
animation script and an ini options file. In the ini file the
animations scripts and the render directory have to be specified. Make
sure that the render directory already exists. To start the
calculation run: 

anitmt-calc inifile.ini 

To render the animation with povray run:

anitmt-view 

If the povray executable is not reachable with the path or if you want
to render only some frames run :

anitmt-view --help

If you don't like to use the -a or -A option to create the avi film,
change to the render directory and use tga2avi (unkompressed avis) or
mkavi (little compressed avis). You get some info about this with:

tga2avi --help
mkavi --help

If you have any questions feel free to send us a mail:
anitmt@theofel.de

We are glad about any kind of feetback.

Have Fun

Jan Theofel
